1
00:00:01,068 --> 00:00:03,003
♪

2
00:00:07,407 --> 00:00:09,442
Girl: Hey, guys, what is this?

3
00:00:09,476 --> 00:00:13,680
Boy: A gate. It connects
the inside and outside.

4
00:00:13,714 --> 00:00:15,049
Girl: Outside?

5
00:00:15,082 --> 00:00:17,585
We’ve never been outside.

6
00:00:17,618 --> 00:00:21,355
Boy 2: That’s because we haven’t
left here since being born.

7
00:00:21,388 --> 00:00:24,558
Girl: So is this what mom
always tells us about?

8
00:00:24,591 --> 00:00:27,260
"Never go near the gate or fence
in the back of the forest,

9
00:00:27,294 --> 00:00:28,695
’cause it’s dangerous."

10
00:00:28,729 --> 00:00:31,465
Boy 1: She says that,
but it’s not true.

11
00:00:31,498 --> 00:00:32,799
Boy 2: It’s not?

12
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:35,869
girl: Hey, ray,
what would you do outside, huh?

13
00:00:35,903 --> 00:00:38,172
Ray: I don’t know. You, Emma?

14
00:00:38,205 --> 00:00:40,174
Emma: I’d ride a giraffe!

15
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:41,542
Ray: Good luck.

16
00:00:43,577 --> 00:00:44,511
Boy: This gate...

17
00:00:45,846 --> 00:00:47,681
You know, I wonder

18
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:50,450
what it’s really
keeping us protected us from.

19
00:00:55,923 --> 00:00:57,858
♪

20
00:01:02,963 --> 00:01:05,432
( Singing in Japanese )

21
00:01:20,714 --> 00:01:21,682
♪ Fire

22
00:01:21,715 --> 00:01:24,384
( singing in Japanese )

23
00:01:30,257 --> 00:01:31,325
♪ It’s on fire

24
00:01:31,358 --> 00:01:33,293
( singing in Japanese )

25
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,268
♪ It’s on fire

26
00:01:41,301 --> 00:01:43,603
( singing in Japanese )

27
00:01:58,619 --> 00:02:00,788
♪ Go to future

28
00:02:00,821 --> 00:02:02,956
( singing in Japanese )

29
00:02:27,047 --> 00:02:28,949
( Clock ticking )

30
00:02:32,085 --> 00:02:34,020
( Ticking continues )

31
00:02:37,691 --> 00:02:39,593
( Bell tolling )

32
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:47,801
Emma: Good morning, everyone!

33
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:50,471
time to get up,
or you’ll miss breakfast!

34
00:02:50,504 --> 00:02:52,373
( Children yawning )

35
00:02:52,406 --> 00:02:54,375
( Overlapping chatter )

36
00:02:54,408 --> 00:02:56,410
- Boy: I’m gonna get you!
- Boy 2: Yeah, right!

37
00:02:56,443 --> 00:02:57,511
- ( Boy 1 laughs )
- Girl: Hey!

38
00:02:57,544 --> 00:02:58,745
Stop messing around,
and get ready!

39
00:02:58,779 --> 00:03:00,547
girl 2: Emma,
I can’t put my shoes on!

40
00:03:00,581 --> 00:03:02,516
Boy 3: I don’t know
how to tie the laces!

41
00:03:02,549 --> 00:03:05,118
Emma: I’ll help you in a second.
There’s no need to cry.

42
00:03:05,152 --> 00:03:07,054
( Overlapping chatter )

43
00:03:09,156 --> 00:03:11,458
Emma: Good morning, Don!
morning, conny!

44
00:03:11,491 --> 00:03:12,726
You, too, little bunny!

45
00:03:12,759 --> 00:03:13,727
Don: Good morning!

46
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,761
Conny: Good morning, Emma.

47
00:03:16,096 --> 00:03:17,898
emma: Look.
We’re here just in time.

48
00:03:17,931 --> 00:03:19,733
( Boys grunt )

49
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:21,601
( Boys laugh )

50
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:24,071
( Emma chuckles )

51
00:03:24,104 --> 00:03:26,873
Now you’ve done it. ( Growls )

52
00:03:26,907 --> 00:03:28,475
I’m gonna eat you!

53
00:03:28,509 --> 00:03:30,478
Girl 1: And off they go again.

54
00:03:30,511 --> 00:03:32,013
( All laughing )

55
00:03:35,916 --> 00:03:36,884
Boys: Yeah!

56
00:03:36,917 --> 00:03:39,686
Emma: Hey, guys! Good morning!

57
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,222
Boy 4: Hi, Emma. Morning.

58
00:03:41,255 --> 00:03:43,023
Ray: Good morning, Emma.

59
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,658
Boy 4: You’re so full of energy,

60
00:03:44,691 --> 00:03:46,226
and you haven’t even had
your breakfast yet.

61
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:48,996
ray: Come on.
How old are you, five?

62
00:03:49,029 --> 00:03:51,031
Emma: I’m 11, same as you guys

63
00:03:51,064 --> 00:03:53,567
and one of the oldest kids here!

64
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,634
( Woman laughs )

65
00:03:54,668 --> 00:03:56,603
Emma: You’re laughing, too, mom?

66
00:03:56,637 --> 00:03:58,706
Mom: Emma, come help me out.

67
00:03:58,739 --> 00:04:00,107
Emma: In a minute!

68
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:02,976
I wanna redo my entrance,
’cause ray teased me!

69
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:06,680
Mom: Why change it? It showed
just what I love about you.

70
00:04:06,713 --> 00:04:09,115
emma: That i’m
five years old at heart?

71
00:04:09,149 --> 00:04:11,618
mom: Mm-mmm.
That isn’t what I meant.

72
00:04:11,652 --> 00:04:14,588
i love how deeply
you care about your family.

73
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:18,692
Emma: Thank you, mom. I’m glad.

74
00:04:18,725 --> 00:04:20,126
( Giggles )

75
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:22,096
( Bell rings )

76
00:04:23,197 --> 00:04:26,033
Mom: Good morning to you,
my darling children.

77
00:04:26,066 --> 00:04:29,036
Now let us appreciate
that all 38 of you

78
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:32,306
are able to live happy lives
under this roof.

79
00:04:33,473 --> 00:04:35,141
We are thankful.

80
00:04:35,175 --> 00:04:37,444
Children: Thank you
for our breakfast.

81
00:04:37,477 --> 00:04:38,979
♪

82
00:04:43,517 --> 00:04:44,685
Mom: Now open wide.

83
00:04:44,718 --> 00:04:45,686
Conny: Ahh.

84
00:04:45,719 --> 00:04:47,654
( Overlapping chatter )

85
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:51,224
Yummy!

86
00:04:51,258 --> 00:04:53,227
Mom: You’re acting
like a little baby,

87
00:04:53,260 --> 00:04:54,528
aren’t you, conny?

88
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:56,763
Conny: It’s okay, right?
Especially today!

89
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,299
Mom: Of course.

90
00:04:58,332 --> 00:05:00,334
Recording: Age 11, type one.

91
00:05:00,367 --> 00:05:02,736
Answer each question
within ten seconds.

92
00:05:02,769 --> 00:05:05,272
When you hear the tone, begin.

93
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,540
( Buzzer )

94
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:08,642
( Timer ticking )

95
00:05:08,675 --> 00:05:11,545
( Scanner whirring )

96
00:05:11,578 --> 00:05:13,680
♪

97
00:05:15,582 --> 00:05:17,117
( Girl 2 sighs )

98
00:05:18,185 --> 00:05:19,119
( Boy 3 grunts )

99
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:26,660
( Buzzer )

100
00:05:26,693 --> 00:05:29,296
( Girl 1 sighs )

101
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:30,897
( Groans )

102
00:05:30,931 --> 00:05:33,333
Boy 1: Well, I think
I got at least half.

103
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:35,402
Boy 5: That many? Wow!

104
00:05:35,435 --> 00:05:38,638
Conny: I’m jealous. I didn’t
get most of the questions.

105
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:41,341
Mom: Let’s quiet down
and go through the results.

106
00:05:41,375 --> 00:05:44,378
Norman, ray, Emma,

107
00:05:44,411 --> 00:05:46,146
perfect scores again!

108
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:48,182
Fantastic! I’m so proud!

109
00:05:48,215 --> 00:05:50,718
- Emma: Yay!
- ( Children murmuring )

110
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:53,654
boy 6: None of us
even come close to those three.

111
00:05:53,687 --> 00:05:56,456
norman alone’s
smarter than all of us combined,

112
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:58,192
and then there’s ray,

113
00:05:58,225 --> 00:06:00,694
who’s good at solving
any problem he’s faced with.

114
00:06:00,727 --> 00:06:03,196
to top it off,
Emma learns really fast,

115
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:05,199
so she can keep up
with them, easy.

116
00:06:05,232 --> 00:06:07,434
Girl 1: They say
the house has never had

117
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:09,569
three kids at this level
together before.

118
00:06:09,603 --> 00:06:11,572
Boy 6: Then, no wonder
mom’s proud of them.

119
00:06:11,605 --> 00:06:13,340
- Don: Norman!
- Norman: Hmm?

120
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:15,508
Don: I’m challenging you to tag!

121
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:16,810
( Norman chuckles )

122
00:06:16,844 --> 00:06:18,946
( Children cheering, yelling )

123
00:06:24,985 --> 00:06:27,888
( Watch ticking )

124
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:30,491
( Norman grunts )

125
00:06:31,992 --> 00:06:33,727
( Ray sighs )

126
00:06:46,974 --> 00:06:47,942
( Children yelp )

127
00:06:47,975 --> 00:06:49,443
Don: Come get us, Norman!

128
00:06:49,476 --> 00:06:51,712
We’ll outrun you
this time for sure!

129
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:53,680
Right, conny?

130
00:06:53,714 --> 00:06:56,584
Conny: Don, thanks for always
being there to help me.

131
00:06:56,617 --> 00:06:58,686
Don: Nah, you don’t
have to thank me.

132
00:06:58,719 --> 00:07:02,556
I’ll always help anytime,
anywhere you need me.

133
00:07:02,589 --> 00:07:03,557
( Conny giggles ) Shh.

134
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:05,025
( Don gasps )

135
00:07:06,126 --> 00:07:08,328
Eh? Oh.

136
00:07:08,362 --> 00:07:09,663
( Conny groans )

137
00:07:09,696 --> 00:07:11,898
Don: Judging from the size
of these footprints...

138
00:07:11,932 --> 00:07:13,400
( Chuckles )

139
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,335
You let your guard down, Norman.

140
00:07:15,369 --> 00:07:16,337
- ( Conny chuckles )

141
00:07:16,370 --> 00:07:17,404
- ( Don gasps )

142
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:19,940
Norman: No, Don. You did.

143
00:07:22,042 --> 00:07:23,677
I tell you this every time.

144
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:26,446
Your weakness is that you
make a judgment too quickly

145
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,449
and then lose your cool.
( Chuckles )

146
00:07:28,482 --> 00:07:29,450
( Don sighs )

147
00:07:29,483 --> 00:07:31,018
( Overlapping chatter )

148
00:07:31,051 --> 00:07:34,054
don: What the heck?
He got practically everyone!

149
00:07:34,087 --> 00:07:35,855
Boy 6: That happens
when norman’s it.

150
00:07:35,889 --> 00:07:37,791
Girl 3: There’s only
one survivor left.

151
00:07:37,824 --> 00:07:40,160
Girl 1: Yeah.
Emma’s still going!

152
00:07:40,194 --> 00:07:42,730
♪

153
00:07:45,065 --> 00:07:46,099
Emma: Oh.

154
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:47,801
( Chuckles )

155
00:07:47,835 --> 00:07:49,136
( Norman chuckles )

156
00:08:05,919 --> 00:08:07,821
( Ticking )

157
00:08:17,865 --> 00:08:19,767
( Emma chuckles )

158
00:08:21,201 --> 00:08:22,536
- ( Norman groans )
- ( Emma gasps )

159
00:08:25,539 --> 00:08:26,507
Norman!

160
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:28,208
Norman: Just pretending.

161
00:08:28,242 --> 00:08:31,679
emma: What?!
You had me worried about you!

162
00:08:31,712 --> 00:08:34,582
Norman: Emma. Your weakness
is that you’re too nice.

163
00:08:34,615 --> 00:08:35,850
( Emma gasps )

164
00:08:35,883 --> 00:08:38,185
I can’t believe
he caught me again!

165
00:08:38,218 --> 00:08:41,121
Why do I keep losing?!
So frustrating.

166
00:08:41,154 --> 00:08:42,856
Ray: Question.

167
00:08:42,890 --> 00:08:45,192
What’s Norman good at
that you’re not?

168
00:08:45,225 --> 00:08:46,193
Emma: Hmm.

169
00:08:46,226 --> 00:08:48,095
Uh, planning ahead

170
00:08:48,128 --> 00:08:49,863
and staying calm?

171
00:08:49,897 --> 00:08:52,299
I guess he’s also good
at being smart.

172
00:08:52,332 --> 00:08:54,201
Ray: It’s strategy.

173
00:08:54,234 --> 00:08:57,137
Just think. If it’s about
simple physical ability,

174
00:08:57,171 --> 00:09:00,641
then you have the upper hand,
but it’s more than that.

175
00:09:00,674 --> 00:09:03,210
Norman has brains like no other,

176
00:09:03,243 --> 00:09:06,146
and tag is a game
where you compete with strategy.

177
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:07,848
Emma: In a game of tag?

178
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:09,950
Ray: Way I see it,
tag’s like chess,

179
00:09:09,983 --> 00:09:11,651
but using your whole body.

180
00:09:11,685 --> 00:09:13,120
Don’t you think so, Norman?

181
00:09:13,153 --> 00:09:14,955
Norman: Yeah, sure. But i’d say

182
00:09:14,988 --> 00:09:17,224
that you’re more of a tactician
than I am, ray.

183
00:09:17,257 --> 00:09:18,759
Ray: I don’t know about that.

184
00:09:18,792 --> 00:09:21,361
Emma: So try to anticipate
the enemy’s moves.

185
00:09:21,395 --> 00:09:23,063
Norman: But still,
we can’t compare

186
00:09:23,096 --> 00:09:24,965
to mom’s ability
to read a situation.

187
00:09:24,998 --> 00:09:26,900
Emma: That’s true.
Come to think of it,

188
00:09:26,934 --> 00:09:29,737
none of us have ever been able
to beat her at chess, huh?

189
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:31,705
- ( Norman chuckles )
- ( Ray sighs )

190
00:09:31,738 --> 00:09:33,907
Don: Norman! Rematch!

191
00:09:33,941 --> 00:09:36,243
Next game, everyone is
gonna be it but you!

192
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:37,811
Emma: Calm down!

193
00:09:37,845 --> 00:09:39,847
girl 1:
Don’s all worked up again.

194
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,849
( Norman grunts )

195
00:09:41,882 --> 00:09:43,817
( Birds chirping )

196
00:09:47,888 --> 00:09:50,157
( Boy 3 pants )

197
00:09:56,263 --> 00:09:57,197
( Emma gasps )

198
00:10:00,334 --> 00:10:02,837
( Footsteps echoing )

199
00:10:20,454 --> 00:10:22,957
♪

200
00:10:29,463 --> 00:10:31,398
( Normal footsteps )

201
00:10:34,935 --> 00:10:36,370
( Norman sighs )

202
00:10:39,273 --> 00:10:41,041
Guess you caught me.

203
00:10:41,074 --> 00:10:43,443
♪

204
00:10:43,477 --> 00:10:46,013
Emma: "Never go near
the gate or fence."

205
00:10:46,046 --> 00:10:48,181
norman: Yeah,
mom always tells us that,

206
00:10:48,215 --> 00:10:50,984
because going near there
can be very dangerous.

207
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:53,487
Ray: She says that,
but it’s not even true.

208
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,922
Norman: What do
you mean by that?

209
00:10:55,956 --> 00:10:57,257
Ray: Well, look at it.

210
00:10:57,291 --> 00:10:59,860
What part of this
do you find dangerous?

211
00:10:59,893 --> 00:11:01,228
The fence is low,

212
00:11:01,261 --> 00:11:03,263
and I don’t see
anything remotely threatening.

213
00:11:03,297 --> 00:11:05,466
Emma: But we should do
what mom told us.

214
00:11:05,499 --> 00:11:07,868
ray: Uh-huh.
You really love mom, don’t you?

215
00:11:07,901 --> 00:11:09,870
- Emma: Sure! Everybody does!
- Don: Hey!

216
00:11:09,903 --> 00:11:12,272
What are you guys
doing way back here?

217
00:11:12,306 --> 00:11:14,475
Girl 1: Oh, is the game over?

218
00:11:14,508 --> 00:11:16,243
Norman: We should call it a day.

219
00:11:16,276 --> 00:11:19,012
If we’re out too late,
mom will be worried about us.

220
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,915
Don: Someday...

221
00:11:21,949 --> 00:11:23,884
We’ll have to leave here,
won’t we?

222
00:11:23,917 --> 00:11:27,120
Boy 6: This is an orphanage.
Of course we’ll leave one day,

223
00:11:27,154 --> 00:11:29,223
by the time we turn 12.

224
00:11:29,256 --> 00:11:31,024
Girl 1: You know, it’s weird.

225
00:11:31,058 --> 00:11:34,028
none of us
have ever gotten any letters.

226
00:11:34,061 --> 00:11:35,129
- Emma: Letters?
- Girl 1: Yeah,

227
00:11:35,162 --> 00:11:37,131
nothing from any
of our siblings

228
00:11:37,164 --> 00:11:39,233
who’ve been adopted
over the years.

229
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:41,568
Norman: Oh, that? I’m sure
they’re just being considerate

230
00:11:41,602 --> 00:11:43,104
to their foster parents.

231
00:11:43,136 --> 00:11:45,405
don: But, still,
we were brought here as babies.

232
00:11:45,439 --> 00:11:47,174
We’re the only family we know.

233
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:48,909
Even if we aren’t blood-related,

234
00:11:48,942 --> 00:11:50,877
we’re truer siblings than most!

235
00:11:50,911 --> 00:11:53,614
Girl 1: Maybe the outside world
is so incredible

236
00:11:53,647 --> 00:11:56,483
that they’ve forgotten
all about life at the house.

237
00:11:56,517 --> 00:11:59,587
Emma: Well, in that case,
let’s be happy for them.

238
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:02,456
( Girl 1 groans )
I want to go outside soon, too!

239
00:12:02,489 --> 00:12:04,324
boy 6: And what
would you do out there?

240
00:12:04,358 --> 00:12:06,527
Girl 1: Isn’t it obvious?
Try out new clothes.

241
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,629
- Don: This again.
- Girl 1: I deserve to!

242
00:12:08,662 --> 00:12:10,230
We only have this one uniform!

243
00:12:10,264 --> 00:12:13,100
I read a book one time.
It said the outside world

244
00:12:13,133 --> 00:12:15,168
has hundreds of clothing designs
and patterns,

245
00:12:15,202 --> 00:12:16,937
and I want to wear them all!

246
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:19,005
Boy 6: I wanna eat
all the yummy food.

247
00:12:19,039 --> 00:12:21,275
don: I can’t wait
to find a cute girl to date.

248
00:12:21,308 --> 00:12:23,477
girl 1: You realize
that’s an insult, don’t you?

249
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:25,479
Don: Oh, I didn’t
mean it like that.

250
00:12:25,512 --> 00:12:27,280
Boy 3: I want to see a train!

251
00:12:27,314 --> 00:12:29,216
Don: Hmm, that’s a good one.

252
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:30,484
Emma: And what about you?

253
00:12:30,517 --> 00:12:32,753
norman: Oh,
well, I want to travel,

254
00:12:32,786 --> 00:12:35,489
to see places
i’ve never been to before.

255
00:12:35,522 --> 00:12:37,491
Emma: Nice! And you, ray?

256
00:12:37,524 --> 00:12:39,626
Ray: Once outside...

257
00:12:41,094 --> 00:12:43,096
