what about them?

387
00:20:17,618 --> 00:20:19,820
( Sobs ) I can’t leave them.

388
00:20:19,853 --> 00:20:22,889
if we do,
they’ll all be killed for sure.

389
00:20:22,923 --> 00:20:24,758
I can’t take it.

390
00:20:24,791 --> 00:20:26,793
I don’t want to lose
any more family.

391
00:20:26,827 --> 00:20:28,162
( Norman shudders )

392
00:20:28,195 --> 00:20:30,130
( Hummed melody continues )

393
00:20:33,734 --> 00:20:36,804
And you won’t have to.

394
00:20:36,837 --> 00:20:37,805
( Emma gasps )

395
00:20:41,742 --> 00:20:43,010
Norman: Try not to worry.

396
00:20:43,043 --> 00:20:45,145
We’ll flee, all of us.

397
00:20:45,179 --> 00:20:47,715
Emma: Really? But how?

398
00:20:47,748 --> 00:20:51,185
